Spring init-method and destroy example
====================================================

In Spring you can use methods:

	init()
	destroy()


as atributes in bean configuration files for beans
to perform certain actions upon the initialization
and destruction of beans.  It is an alternative
to interfaces :
	InitializingBean
	DisposableBean



///Code

package com.mkyong.customer.services;

public class CustomerService
{
	String message;

	public String getMessage() {
	  return message;
	}

	public void setMessage(String message) {
	  this.message = message;
	}

	public void initIt() throws Exception {
	  System.out.println("Init method after properties are set : " + message);
	}

	public void cleanUp() throws Exception {
	  System.out.println("Spring Container is destroy! Customer clean up");
	}

}



###File: Spring-Customer.xml, definited init-method and
#########destroy-method attribute in your bean

<beans xmlns="http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans"
	xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
	xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans
	http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans/spring-beans-2.5.xsd">

	<bean id="customerService" class="com.mkyong.customer.services.CustomerService"
		init-method="initIt" destroy-method="cleanUp">

		<property name="message" value="i'm property message" />
	</bean>

</beans>